('F008-011.jpg', NULL, '', 'Roundtower', '', 'Roundtowers were built in Ireland during the 7th and 8th century.\r\nAll monasteries had one.\r\nThey were the last refuge of the monks in case of an raid by wikings.\r\nThe entrance was in 10m height and accessible only with a wooden ladder, which was dragged inside in case of emergency.', '', 'Mathias Duckeck', '', '', ''),
