('F004-042.jpg', NULL, 'Ajanta Caves', 'Porch of the Chaitya Cave Temple', '', 'This engraving shows the facade of one of the Ajanta temples.\r\nIt is from the book:<br>\r\nDr <b class=\"smallCaps\">G Hartwig</b> (1871):\r\n    <b>The Subterranean World</b>,\r\n    <br>\r\n    First New York Edition, 522 pp 78 steel engravings. 3 colour maps. HB gilt stamped dark brown cloth, bookplate, light wear. G<br>\r\n    Marvellous touch of Victoriana with descriptions and illustrations of Aggtelek, Mammoth, Fingal’s,  Adelsburg etc.  With detailed accounts of numerous other caves.   \r\n', '', '', '', '', ''),
('306-040.jpg', NULL, 'Altamira', 'Bison', 'Bison', 'This Bison from Altamira is a copy which is located at the Deutsches Museum (German Museum) in Munich, Germany.\r\nA part of the ceiling was copied, including the relief of teh cave wall, to given an extremely realistic impression of Altamira.\r\nThis copy was the first of its kind, using modern technology like photogrammetry. It was made after the cave was closed for visitors to protect the drawings. The Deutsches Museum made a copy for the Spanish government and a second one for their own museum.', '', 'Jochen Duckeck', '', '', ''),
