('070-919.jpg', NULL, 'Aranui Cave', 'Soda Straw', 'Soda Straw', 'Soda straws are formed by a drop of water depositing a circle of calcite.\r\nThis circle grows to form a thin tube.\r\nThe Straw on this image is about 4-5mm in diameter and 30cm long.', 'Sinterröhrchen bilden sich durch einen Wassertropfen, der etwas Kalzit kreisrund um sich herum ablagert.\r\nDer Kreis wird schnell zu einem Röhrchen.\r\nDieses hier hat etwa 4-5mm Durchmesser und ist etwa 30cm lang.', 'Jochen Duckeck', '', '', ''),
('270-024.jpg', NULL, 'Laichinger Tiefenhöhle', 'Great Hall', 'Große Halle', 'The biggest chamber of the cave, 45m below surface.', '', 'Jochen Duckeck', '', '', ''),
('070-917.jpg', NULL, 'Aranui Cave', 'Soda Straw', '', 'The horizontal rims are either harder layers of rocks, or speleothems formed by water emerging from a horiziontal cleft.', '', 'Jochen Duckeck', '', '', ''),
('D082-0082.jpg', NULL, 'Postojnska Jama', 'Natural Entrance', 'Natürlicher Eingang', 'This is the natural entrance to the cave system of Postojna.\r\nAt the border between <b>flysh</b> on the left side and <b>limestone</b> on the right side, the water of the river Pivka enters the limestone karst.\r\nSo the entrance is also the sink of the Pivka river.\r\nThe layers are tilted, and the profile of the cave entrance follows a bedding plane.', '', 'Jochen Duckeck', '', '', ''),
('D082-0076.jpg', NULL, 'Postojnska Jama', 'Historic Entrance', '', 'This entrance of the cave leads to the upper, fossil level.\r\nIt was once used to visit the cave, but today it is the exit.\r\nSo this is the view one has when leaving the cave.', '', 'Jochen Duckeck', '', '', ''),
('D082-0033.jpg', NULL, 'Postojnska Jama', 'Formation', '', 'One of numerous formations in Postojnska Jama.', '', 'Jochen Duckeck', '', '', ''),
('D082-0016.jpg', NULL, 'Postojnska Jama', 'Calvary', '', 'The Calvary is a mountain of debris in a huge chamber, which is covered with stalagmites. The name calavary is a remains of the Austro-Hungarian history and used very frequent in Slovenia. There is virtually no cave without one.', '', 'Jochen Duckeck', '', '', ''),
('D082-0020.jpg', NULL, 'Postojnska Jama', 'The Russian Bridge', '', 'This view down the Calvary to the Russian Bridge is rather impressive.\r\nTiny formations on the walls are several meters long if you look closer.\r\nThe Russian Bridge was named after Russian pioneers who built it during World War I.', '', 'Jochen Duckeck', '', '', ''),
('D082-0035.jpg', NULL, 'Postojnska Jama', 'Speleothems', '', 'This are pure white stalagmites in the so-called Beautiful Passage, probably the most beautiful part of Postojnska Jama.', '', 'Jochen Duckeck', '', '', ''),
('D082-0039.jpg', NULL, 'Postojnska Jama', 'Beatiful Caves', '', 'This is the end of the passage called Beatiful Caves. \r\nThis last chaber has rather view formations, but an impressive profile and size.', '', 'Jochen Duckeck', '', '', ''),
('D082-0043.jpg', NULL, 'Postojnska Jama', 'Great Mountain or Calvary', '', 'The Great Mountain or Calvary and the walls of this chaber are covered with speleothems.\r\nThis is a view from the Calvary to the wal, showing how stalactites grow along fissures in the rock where enter the cave.', '', 'Jochen Duckeck', '', '', ''),
('D082-0051.jpg', NULL, 'Postojnska Jama', 'The Russian Bridge', '', 'This bridge was built during World War II by Russian prisoners of war. This is the bridge from below.', '', 'Jochen Duckeck', '', '', ''),
('D082-0055.jpg', NULL, 'Postojnska Jama', 'Beatiful Caves', '', 'The Beatiful Caves are named such because of the abundance of flowstone.', '', 'Jochen Duckeck', '', '', ''),
('D082-0056.jpg', NULL, 'Postojnska Jama', 'The Diamond', '', 'This group of a pure white stalagmite and a brown pillar is the most famous speleothem of Postojnska Jama, as it was used for advertisement since the mid 20th century.', '', 'Jochen Duckeck', '', '', ''),
('D082-0057.jpg', NULL, 'Postojnska Jama', 'The White Passage', '', 'This part of Postojnska Jama is praised for the overwhelming white speleothems, including stalactites, stalagmited, draperies and curtains.', '', 'Jochen Duckeck', '', '', ''),
('D082-0060.jpg', NULL, 'Postojnska Jama', 'Proteus anguinus', '', 'This huge chamber is despite its sheer size notable for the small pool in the middle, which contains rare olms (Proteus anguinus), an amphibic salamander.', '', 'Jochen Duckeck', '', '', ''),
('D082-0058.jpg', NULL, 'Postoinska Jama', 'Proteus anguinus', 'Proteus anguinus', 'The olm or proteus is an amphibic animal similar to the salamander, living only in the Dinaric Karst. It is a true troglobiont without eyes and pigmentation and endimic for this area.\r\nHere it is shown to visitors on the guided tour through Postojnska Jama. The last chamber has a pool in the middle where several olms can be seen. They are catched in a cave nearby and released into freedom after a few weeks.', '', 'Jochen Duckeck', '', '', ''),
('D082-0068.jpg', NULL, '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Jochen Duckeck', NULL, NULL, NULL),
('D082-0008.jpg', NULL, 'Eisriesenwelt', 'Werfen Mountains', 'Werfengebirge', 'A view on the Werfengebirge from Werfen.\r\nSomewhere up there is the entrance to the Eisriesenwelt.', 'Ein Blick auf das Werfengebirge von Werfen aus.\r\nDort oben befindet sich der Eingang zur Eisriesenwelt.', 'Jochen Duckeck', '', '', ''),
('D082-0061.jpg', NULL, 'Postojnska Jama', 'Underground Train Station', '', 'This is the underground train station, where visitors embark for the ride back to the surface.', '', 'Jochen Duckeck', '', '', ''),
('D082-0009.jpg', NULL, 'Postojnska Jama', 'Map of Notrjanski Kras', '', 'This map of the Notrjanski Kras is located in front of the Postojnska Jama.', '', 'Jochen Duckeck', '', '', ''),
('070-916.jpg', NULL, 'Aranui Cave', 'Pure White Formation', '', 'The speleothems in Aranui Cave or often very pure white. The central stalactite is of an older generation, and after it was formed, the conditions in the cave changed and it stopped growing. But then cave coral started to grow on the surface of the stalactite. There are also younger stalactites, which are not covered by cave coral.', '', 'Jochen Duckeck', '', '', ''),
